definition: to let off/to give out
to put/to place/to release/to free/to let go/to let out/to set off (fireworks)

to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc
variant of 出[chu1] (classifier for plays or chapters of classical novels)
to release from jail

sentences.english: Nitroglycerine is discharged from the bottom of the tank and passes to the filters.
sentences.chinese: 硝化甘油可自槽底放出进入过滤器。

sentences.english: America is the country that helped liberate a continent from the march of a madman.
sentences.chinese: 美国曾帮助把一个大陆从一个狂人的铁蹄下解放出来。

sentences.english: This therefore frees the pilot to concentrate on his intended tasks during the combat.
sentences.chinese: 这样可以将飞行员在战时解放出来更关注于他的任务。

sentences.english: He straightened his back, his fingers freeing nylon line from a speedily revolving reel.
sentences.chinese: 他直起腰身，用手指快速地从绕线轮上放出尼龙线。

sentences.english: It is hard to free fools from the chains they revere.
sentences.chinese: 将愚人从他们所敬拜的锁链下解放出来是非常困难的。

sentences.english: Let the water out of the bathtub.
The underlying strength of the U. S. economy is gradually re-asserting itself.
sentences.chinese: 美国经济的内在活力又一次逐渐释放出来了。

sentences.english: There is the promise of how he sets us free.
sentences.chinese: 希望就是他如何将我们解放出来。

sentences.english: So point one, that’s what the Cross frees us from.
sentences.chinese: 因此，第一点就是“十字架将我们从何境地解放出来。

sentences.english: It’s unlocking all this great potential that the kids have.
sentences.chinese: 机器人能把孩子们全部巨大潜力尽数释放出来。

sentences.english: Contact with water liberates toxic, highly flammable gas.
sentences.chinese: 与水接触释放出有毒的，极易燃气体。

sentences.english: Feng ghost of smoke, ready to attack.
sentences.chinese: 鬼凤放出烟雾，准备偷袭。

sentences.english: We'll post an image of the netherwhelp, offspring of the nether drake flying mount, in the near future.
sentences.chinese: 我们将在捎后放出虚空飞龙幼崽的资料。

sentences.english: Is there some set-point which when crossed unleashes the evil?
sentences.chinese: 有没有一个临界点，当它被跨过之后就会释放出邪恶？

sentences.english: Poison is released through a channel in the snake's fangs.
sentences.chinese: 毒液通过蛇牙里的一条导管被释放出来。

sentences.english: He opened the window to free the room of smoke.
sentences.chinese: 他打开窗户把屋里的烟放出去。
